<br>
I see this as narrow minded thinking. Let me explain....<br>
If the raid needs the wiz to use the anti-gate spells in the encounter then great. If the wiz needs to be nuking and casting the anti gate spells, then you need to bring allong two or more wizzies. Making us an asset in numbers. <br>
<br>
We need to get out of this solo mentality and look at the bigger picture. The spell seems to be helping out the wizard class and not necessaraly YOU as a solo wizard.<br>
<br>
If the clerics/chanters/wizards (and everyone else who previously needed to cast stun splls to prevent gating) dont have to spend mana on trying to get the mob to not gate then they can put that mana to better use elsewhare.<br>
<br>
IMHO look at the larger picture (all the wizards in the comunity) and try not to focus on yourself (the solo wizard) too much.<br>
